```python
for i in range(21, 41):
    if i != 2 and i != 3 and (i-1)%2 == 0:  # i is not a prime number
        root = int(i**0.5)
        if root*root == i-1:  # i is one more than a square number
            print(f"The number is {i}.")
            break
```

This program iterates over the numbers from 21 to 40 (inclusive). For each number, it checks if it is not a prime number and if it is one more than a square number. If both conditions are met, it prints the number.
